     <div class="tab">
       <h2>History</h2>
       <p>Hamilton, Scotland. Originally know as Cadzow however in 1455 the name was changed to Hamilton. Cadzow had been around since 568AD and contains a histroy rich in royalty.
          Robert the Bruce gave orders to have the area built in the 12th century and kept the name Cadzow until 1455. in 1455 Lord Hamilton renamed the town Hamilton. </p>
     <div>

     <input type="radio" id="tabvisit" name="mytabs"
     <label for="tabvisit">Visit</label>
     <div class="tab">
       <h2>Visit Hamilton</h2>
       <p> Whilst in Hamilton it would be worth your time to visit Cadzow Castle. Mary Queen of Scots took refuge after fleeing Loch Leven Castle in 1568. Strathclyde park
           is a lovely and quiet walk. The walk lasts around 1hr 30mins and wraps around a small lake. During summer various activities such as paddle boarding take place on
           the lake making it a great day out to take the family</p>
